The paper deals with community detection in complex networks, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper specifically mentions social and information networks as examples of network categories. The second most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as community detection is a common task in software engineering for analyzing software systems. The third most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper discusses different generative models for complex networks. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with communication networks. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as community detection is a problem in graph theory and algorithms for analyzing graphs.
